arStrings.szText: "I found the cleaver. Along with a spirit trapped inside."
You don't say! Who was he? A husband? A lover? I can't say I'm surprised.
Khaliun came to be known far and wide for the number of lovers she had, each disappearing after the next...
Like a storyeller spinning a tale; a bit dramatic
Legend has it she was corrupted by wild jealousy - no doubt the work of the cleaver - and inevitably offed every last partner and paramour.
Spooky, as if telling a tale; a bit gleeful
Then, in order to keep them together forever, she'd consume their flesh so they'd never be apart. Aww.
Continuing his spooky storytelling. The "Aww" at the end is like "Isn't that sweet?" Though the story is morbid.
Though unfortunately, that means these poor souls will never truly find rest. Ah, well. At least you've brought the cleaver to me, so I can keep it safe from any more... victims.
Mischievous. He's not that torn up about "these poor souls" as he delights in the dark history of these artifacts.
